Your cluster "{{ .Kind.Name }}" is ready.

Everything has been deployed in the `gravitee` namespace.

{{ if not (hasFlag "disable-ui") -}}
APIM Console     http://localhost:30080
{{ end -}}
{{ if and (not (hasFlag "disable-portal")) (not (hasFlag "disable-ui")) -}}
APIM Portal      http://localhost:30081
{{ end -}}
APIM Gateway     http://localhost:30082
Management API   http://localhost:30083
{{ if hasFlag "enable-hc-vault" -}}

Vault is deployed in dev mode (root token: root).
To access the Vault API/UI from your host:

  kubectl port-forward svc/vault -n gravitee 8200:8200
{{ end -}}
{{ if not (hasFlag "disable-kafka") -}}

Kafka Gateway    *.kafka.sew.local:9092 (TLS)

To connect a Kafka client to the gateway, extract the TLS certificate:

  kubectl get secret kafka-tls -n gravitee -o jsonpath='{.data.tls\.crt}' | base64 -d > kafka-tls.crt

Then use these client properties:

  security.protocol=SSL
  ssl.truststore.type=PEM
  ssl.truststore.location=/path/to/kafka-tls.crt
  ssl.endpoint.identification.algorithm=
{{ end -}}
{{ if hasFlag "enable-alert-engine" -}}

Alert Engine is running inside the cluster (ws://alert-engine:8072).
{{ end -}}
